DO’s and DONT’s of Social Media


DO’s	  

1]  Do audit your privacy settings regularly. Ensure you know exactly who can see your personal posts, tags, and photos.	
2] Do showcase your achievements. Use platforms like LinkedIn to highlight your projects, volunteer work, and academic successes.	
3] Do think before you share. Always ask yourself: "Would I be comfortable with everyone seeing this?"
4] Do engage positively with others. Lift up your peers, congratulate people on their wins, and share valuable, insightful content.	
5] Do keep a professional profile picture. Ensure the avatars on your public-facing accounts are clear, appropriate, and friendly.	

DONT's
1] Don't post in the heat of the moment. Never use social media to vent while angry, frustrated, or overly emotional.
2] Don't bash professors, peers, or employers. Complaining about your school or job online is highly unprofessional and leaves a digital paper trail.
3] Don't share sensitive or confidential info. Avoid posting pictures of ID cards, offer letters with salary details, or proprietary company data.
4] Don't engage with internet trolls. Avoid getting pulled into hostile arguments or public comment-section fights.
5] Don't assume your "private" posts are fully private. Screenshots exist; always assume anything you put on the internet can become public.

